parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring insulation can cause electrical shorts, leading to excessive fuel being fed to the engine, which can cause the engine to rev and jerk while driving, potentially leading to loss of control and accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potentially stranding the driver. Repeated attempts to replace the starter motor can also cause damage to the flywheel, leading to additional repair costs.
symptoms: the starter motor does not engage properly
the starter motor clashes with the flywheel
